We are so excited to finally announce a new creative endeavor: ✨@troubled.makers ✨

Visit your fav (self-proclaimed) fun couple at our first lil disturbed vendor booth THIS Saturday at the Los Feliz Flea Market!

Our relationship has always revolved around being creative together and truly loving each other’s fucked up minds. When we (@danadrewdles and @chriscanbefunny) fell head-over -clown-shoes for each other, we were writing and performing comedy in Boston. Five years of new adventures, jobs, businesses, a pandemic, a cross-country move, and three adopted creatures later, we’ve been craving a new exciting and risky and probably dumb challenge that gets us creating more regularly again.

As two expert gift-givers (seriously, we basically compete with each other at this point) and true maximalists at heart, we’ve talked about opening a gift store since our first date. So, we took the plunge and now our 400 square foot apartment is nearly impossible to move in. But we’re so fucking excited.

Please follow @troubled.makers and stay tuned for product pictures, ways to shop, and how to get a custom piece from two Trouble[d] Makers with a gift for gifting!!! 🥳

I am buzzing with excitement (heh) over my gifts from my BFFs at @vush_official and so frickin’ pumped to have another huge discount code for my internet friends💰

To put it bluntly: I’m on antidepressants and Vush still does NOT disappoint…

But, not only does Vush make stellar products, they’re also a brand that you can feel reallyyy solid about supporting with me because of their progressive priorities:

• Help users unlearn the internalized shame of loving or even knowing our own bodies
• Focus on gender-neutral tech and language
• Produce and manufacture responsibly (which, as a business owner, I know gets pricey) while still keeping products accessible

So check out the link in my story and get 40% off Myth, Muse, Majesty 2, and/or Rose 2 toy from the next-gen line today using DANAD40! Offer valid until midnight PST on Thursday, January 5th or while supplies last. 

As always, thank you for supporting my partnerships and helping to amplify brands that actually make the world a better place.

tbh being a freelance creative can be a real uphill battle... but sometimes it means going to a buzzing cafe on a sunny day to illustrate consent and french fries for very cool people doing even cooler things.

Working with @FosteringParenthood on their latest campaign put some serious pep back in my step. Here are just a few of the amazing things this podcast does to support and uplift the voices of current (and former!) foster youth and caregivers: 
- Empower listeners with a well-rounded education on sexual and reproductive health
- Offer tips and guidelines for caregivers to have productive and open conversations about tricky topics with their youth
- Equipt foster youth with the tools to make consensual, responsible, and confident choices about their own bodies

Do me and @FosteringParenthood a solid by sharing this, following them, and checking out this awesome podcast. #FosteringParenthood
